notes_display: In Historical Sketches of the Paper Currency of the American Colonies by Henry Phillips, Jr. (1865). Given to Dr. Jesse C. Green in 1890. Leaf 56N.
issue_place_s: Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, United States of America
issue_obverse_legend_s: FIVE SHILLINGS. THIS BILL shall pass current for FIVE SHILLINGS within the Province of Pensilvania, according to an Act of Assembly made in the 32d Year of the Reign of King GEORGE II. Dated April 25, 1759. A CROWN.
issue_reverse_legend_s: FIVE SHILLINGS. | To Counterfeit, is DEATH | Printed by B. FRANKLIN, and D. HALL. 1759.
